2026-04-30: vescCurrentIno.ino — ported PI current controller from PI_Dev/PI_ex1.ino into firmware as a fixed-Hz loop on the ESP32. New protocol: PI_ENABLE/PI_FORCE/PI_TARGET/PI_HZ/PI_GAINS/PI_PARAMS/PI_LIMITS/PI_CONFIG and a PICTRL stream (esp_ms,i_target,i_meas,i_cmd,omega,actual_hz,target_lb). Force→current conversion is one labeled line: g_piTargetAmps = g_pi.amps_per_lb * lbs (default 0.5 A/lb). PI loop owns the VESC UART read; TELEM stream reuses the cached snapshot when PI is on. Link-loss safety: PI self-disables and zeroes current if BLE drops. STOP also disables PI.
2026-04-30: vesc_current_control.py — added Force Control panel (force lbs, Engage/Stop, loop-Hz spinbox + Actual Hz readout, editable Kt/Ke/R/L/Kp/Ki/I_max/A-per-lb/pole-pairs with one-shot Apply, live equation label). Layout cleanup: timed-run + CSV controls promoted out of the commands frame so they apply to all modes; commands frame renamed "Direct command". PICTRL parsed into a 25k-sample deque, plotted as dashed I-target / dotted I-cmd on the existing amps panel, and folded into CSV via device_ms-nearest pairing alongside ENC. CSV gains four columns: force_target_lb, i_target_a, i_cmd_a, omega_rps. PICFG echoes pull config back into the UI so the constants editor mirrors the live ESP32 state.
